subSubSection.paragraph:
Sterile cormoids, similar to the present ones, with hydrothecae provided with exceedingly long lateral nematothecae were already reported notably from Indonesia by Billard (1913) and the Seychelles by Millard & Bouillon (1973) (both as
Halopteris polymorpha var. sibogae
). According to the former author, this character mainly distinguishes his so-called variety from the nominal species.
